scopecontent.p:
Many photographs document farms and ranches related to the Alm and Welsh families and their friends. Sites identified in Montana include the ""Medicine Rocks,"" a series of sandstone pillars near Ekalaka (later encompassed by Medicine Rocks State Park, established in 1957) that also include persons gathering creeping cedar (
                        Juniperus horizontalis
                     ) as well as views of the BN Ranch at Ash Creek and the Sievert Ranch at Nye and discrete views of Terry and Yates. Sites identified in Wisconsin include views of rivers and lakes, including the St. Croix River at Hudson, as well as views of Deronda and Milltown. There are also views of Stillwater in Minnesota and Casselton in North Dakota.
